Package: Rsubread
Type: Package
Title:  Rsubread: a took kit for analyzing next-gen sequencing read data
Version: 1.11.9
Author: Wei Shi and Yang Liao with contributions from Jenny Zhiyin Dai and Timothy Triche, Jr.
Maintainer: Wei Shi <shi@wehi.edu.au>
Description: This R package provides easy-to-use facilities to analyze next-gen sequencing read data including quality assessment, read alignment, read summarization, exon-exon junction detection, absolute expression calling and SNP calling. It supports major sequencing platforms such as Illumina GA/HiSeq, Roche 454, ABI SOLiD and Ion Torrent. It can be run on Linux/Unix and Mac OS X computers.
URL: http://bioconductor.org/packages/release/bioc/html/Rsubread.html
License: GPL-3
LazyLoad: yes
biocViews: Sequencing, HighThroughputSequencing
